== B.1 — Year One Minimum Equipment

All items below are required before beginning Year One Month 3 laboratory work. Sources include laboratory supply companies, online scientific suppliers, and in some cases hardware and kitchen supply stores.

=== Glassware

#table(
  columns: (1fr, auto, 1fr),
  stroke: 0.5pt + ttao-rule,
  fill: (col, row) => if row == 0 { ttao-mid } else if calc.odd(row) { ttao-pale } else { white },
  inset: 0.6em,
  text(fill: white, weight: "bold")[Item],
  text(fill: white, weight: "bold")[Qty],
  text(fill: white, weight: "bold")[Notes],

  [Erlenmeyer flasks, borosilicate — 250ml], [3–4], [For maceration, distillation receiver, storage],
  [Erlenmeyer flasks, borosilicate — 500ml], [3–4], [For maceration and larger volumes],
  [Round-bottom flask, borosilicate — 250ml or 500ml], [1–2], [For distillation and calcination with sand bath],
  [Liebig condenser with water jacket], [1], [Essential for distillation. Must fit flask joint size.],
  [Glass tubing, borosilicate — assorted diameters], [1 set], [For connecting still train; can be bent with torch],
  [Dark glass storage bottles — 250ml], [4–6], [For storing macerate, hydrosol, essence, and salts],
  [Separatory funnel — 100ml or 250ml], [1], [For separating oil layer from hydrosol (Month 9)],
  [Cork and rubber stoppers — assorted], [1 set], [Size to match flask openings; essential for sealing],
  [Parafilm roll], [1], [For additional sealing of long-digestion vessels],
)

=== Heating and Temperature Control

#table(
  columns: (1fr, auto, 1fr),
